## Acknowledgments

The Cheeta Ethical License draws inspiration from:
- The MIT License (permissive spirit)
- The GPL (copyleft concept)
- The Fair Source License (size-based differentiation)
- The Commons Clause (commercial restriction approach)
- The Prosperity Public License (commercial limitations)
- The Elastic License (source-available model)

CEL aims to combine the best aspects of these licenses while addressing their shortcomings, creating a truly sustainable model for open source software.

---

**The Cheeta Ethical License is designed to make open source sustainable.**

Questions? Contact us at legal@cheeta.dev or visit https://cheeta.dev/licenses/cel

